John,

Wanted to give you the market read from Axalta's side as we head into Q4.

The auto body refinish market saw across-the-board price movement in Q3-Q4 2026. Our Cromax line settled at approximately +18% from Q1 reference pricing, driven by:
- Resin input costs up ~14%
- Pigment costs up ~22%
- Freight on aerosol products up ~8%

This is consistent with what PPG, BASF, and the other major coatings vendors have done. The +18% is roughly the market median, with some manufacturers slightly above and some slightly below depending on product mix.

If you ever want to pilot a small Cromax allocation across the three shops, we'd love to bring you over from PPG. Our cycle-time gains on the new XP product line are real and the cost-per-vehicle pickup over PPG is typically 6-8% advantage at current price points.

In any case - good luck with the budget hearing. I know you have a lot on your plate this quarter.

